te renders `Image(mediaGoogIcon)` and `Image(mediaFbIcon)` as placeholder actions only.\"\n-      ],\n-      \"parityLevel\": \"not-applicable\",\n-      \"targetEndpoints\": [\n-        \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/login/login_page.cj::renderLoginRoute\"\n-      ],\n-      \"tests\": [],\n-      \"notes\": \"Static-analysis image-viewer tagging for LoginScreen.kt was a false positive caused by ordinary icon rendering.\"\n-    }\n-    },\n-    {\n-    \"featureId\": \"app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-login-1ed35246b3-002-navigation-surface-menu-drawer-toolbar-o\",\n-    \"set\": {\n-      \"status\": \"implemented\",\n-      \"sourceBehavior\": \"LoginScreen triggers a successful transition to `Screen.Home.route` from the login button callback, popping the start destination so onboarding/login are cleared from the stack instead of remaining on back navigation.\",\n-      \"targetBehavior\": \"The HarmonyOS bootstrap route host keeps login as a dedicated route and, after successful credential validation, navigates directly to the shared home route through the same route contract used by the shell. The login route remains distinct from onboarding/profile and the success path replaces the visible route instead of leaving the user on the login screen.\",\n-      \"verificationEvidence\": [\n-        \"Source review: D:/Kotlin2Cangjie/Foodike/app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/login/LoginScreen.kt calls `navController.navigate(Screen.Home.route)` from `PerformLogin` and uses `popUpTo(navController.graph.findStartDestination().id) { inclusive = true }` to clear the prior flow.\",\n-        \"Target review: entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj::FoodikeBootstrap.performLogin calls `navigateTo(loginStore.successRoute())` only after credential validation succeeds, and entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/login/login_store.cj::successRoute returns the home route contract.\",\n-        \"Test verification: `C:/Users/Sieger/.cangjie-sdk/6.1/cangjie/build-tools/tools/bin/cjpm.exe test --target aarch64-linux-ohos` passed in `D:/workspace/Foodike/Foodike-Harmony/entry`, including `phase03_onboarding_login_profile_test.cj::Phase03OnboardingLoginProfileTest.loginStoreAcceptsOnlySourceCredentials`.\"\n-      ],\n-      \"parityLevel\": \"equivalent\",\n-      \"targetEndpoints\": [\n-        \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj::FoodikeBootstrap.performLogin\",\n-        \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj::FoodikeBootstrap.navigateTo\",\n-        \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/login/login_store.cj::LoginStore.successRoute\",\n-        \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/app_router.cj::routePath\"\n-      ],\n-      \"tests\": [\n-        \"entry/src/test/cangjie/phase03_onboarding_login_profile_test.cj::Phase03OnboardingLoginProfileTest.loginStoreAcceptsOnlySourceCredentials\"\n-      ],\n-      \"notes\": \"The HarmonyOS route host uses a single current-route state instead of a Compose back stack, but the user-visible login-to-home transition contract is preserved.\"\n-    }\n-    },\n-    {\n-    \"featureId\": \"app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-login-5777ecba15-003-notification-widget-remoteviews-or-home\",\n-    \"set\": {\n-      \"status\": \"not-applicable\",\n-      \"sourceBehavior\": \"Source review of LoginScreen.kt found no notification publishing, widget update, RemoteViews, or home-screen integration behavior; the file only renders the login form and placeholder actions.\",\n-      \"targetBehavior\": \"No HarmonyOS notification or widget integration was added for the login route because the inspected source login screen has no such behavior.\",\n-      \"verificationEvidence\": [\n-        \"Source review: D:/Kotlin2Cangjie/Foodike/app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/login/LoginScr