ting only.\",\n-        \"Target review: entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/login/login_page.cj, login_store.cj, and app/bootstrap_page.cj contain no permission APIs or protected platform access.\"\n-      ],\n-      \"parityLevel\": \"not-applicable\",\n-      \"targetEndpoints\": [],\n-      \"tests\": [],\n-      \"notes\": \"Static-analysis permission tagging for LoginScreen.kt was a false positive.\"\n-    }\n-    },\n-    {\n-    \"featureId\": \"app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-login-2c65d08c3b-005-screen-lifecycle-entry-point-initializat\",\n-    \"set\": {\n-      \"status\": \"implemented\",\n-      \"sourceBehavior\": \"LoginScreen performs screen-entry setup by creating scaffold state, wiring a `LaunchedEffect(key1 = true)` collector for one-shot UI events, and applying status/navigation bar colors while the login screen is active.\",\n-      \"targetBehavior\": \"The HarmonyOS bootstrap route host performs login-screen entry setup by seeding dedicated login state fields, clearing stale error state as users edit, and centralizing login actions in the route host so the login page can be entered, dismissed, and revisited cleanly during onboarding/login/profile flow transitions. The target also preserves immediate one-shot user feedback on failed login through toast emission plus the visible inline error banner.\",\n-      \"verificationEvidence\": [\n-        \"Source review: D:/Kotlin2Cangjie/Foodike/app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/login/LoginScreen.kt initializes scaffold state, collects `eventFlow` in `LaunchedEffect`, and configures window colors from the active Activity context.\",\n-        \"Target review: entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj::FoodikeBootstrap.buildLoginRoute, clearLoginError, and performLogin keep route-entry state and one-shot login feedback inside the route host used at runtime.\",\n-        \"Target review: entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/login/login_page.cj::buildLoginErrorBanner and renderLoginRoute preserve screen-local error presentation while bootstrap_page.cj now also emits a toast on invalid login for immediate non-blocking feedback.\",\n-        \"Build verification: translation-inputs/build-reports/phase-03-onboarding-login-profile/build-report.md recorded PASS after the phase-03 login/profile route implementation.\"\n-      ],\n-      \"parityLevel\": \"equivalent\",\n-      \"targetEndpoints\": [\n-        \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj::FoodikeBootstrap.buildLoginRoute\",\n-        \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj::FoodikeBootstrap.clearLoginError\",\n-        \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj::FoodikeBootstrap.performLogin\",\n-        \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/login/login_page.cj::buildLoginErrorBanner\",\n-        \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/login/login_page.cj::renderLoginRoute\"\n-      ],\n-      \"tests\": [],\n-      \"notes\": \"Exact Android window-color lifecycle hooks are platform-specific and not source-critical to the login flow; the preserved contract is screen-entry state initialization plus immediate one-shot feedback while the route is active.\"\n-    }\n-    },\n-    {\n-    \"featureId\": \"app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-login-34c5f4ba3a-006-settings-preferences-option-toggles-or-c\",\n-    \"set\": {\n-      \"status\": \"implemented\",\n-      \"sourceBehavior\": \"Successful login triggers persisted session-state mutation through `LoginViewModel` and `LoginRepository.toggleLoginState()`, so the screen changes a stored login preference rather than only local UI state.\",\n-      \"targetBehavior\": \"Successful login uses `LoginStore.login()` to write the persisted HarmonyOS login preference through `LoginPreferencesService.login(context)`, preserving the source contract that login updates durable session configuration rather than ephemeral page state.\",\n-      \"verificationEvidence\": [\n-        \"Source review: D:/Kotlin2Cangjie/Foodike/app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/login/LoginViewModel.kt validates credentials and then calls `repository.toggleLoginState()` before invoking the success navigation callback.\",\n-        \"Target review: entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/login/login_store.cj::LoginStore.login persists login state through LoginPreferencesService when credentials match.\",\n-        \"Target review: entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/session/login_preferences_service.cj::LoginPreferencesService.login writes `user_login_state=true` into HarmonyOS Preferences and flushes it immediately.\",\n-        \"Test verification: `C:/Users/Sieger/.cangjie-sdk/6.1/cangjie/build-tools/tools/bin/cjpm.exe test --target aarch64-linux-ohos` passed in `D:/workspace/Foodike/Foodike-Harmony/entry`; persisted-login helpers are also covered by phase-02 startup/navigation tests and the phase-03 login credential test.\"\n-      ],\n-      \"parityLevel\": \"equivalent\",\n-      \"targetEndpoints\": [\n-        \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/login/login_store.cj::LoginStore.login\",\n-        \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/session/login_preferences_service.cj::LoginPreferencesService.login\",\n-        \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/data/session/login_preferences_service.cj::LoginPreferencesService.writeLoginState\"\n-      ],\n-      \"tests\": [\n-        \"entry/src/test/cangjie/phase03_onboarding_login_profile_test.cj::Phase03OnboardingLoginProfileTest.loginStoreAcceptsOnlySourceCredentials\",\n-        \"entry/src/test/cangjie/phase02_startup_navigation_test.cj::Phase02StartupNavigationTest.loginStateToggleRuleFlipsBothDirections\"\n-      ],\n-      \"notes\": \"The source repository flips a stored boolean while the target login path writes the successful state directly; both preserve the user-visible persisted-login outcome for this flow.\"\n-    }\n-    },\n-    {\n-    \"featureId\": \"app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-login-78d5c742f4-007-observable-state-viewmodel-flow-livedata\",\n-    \"set\": {\n-      \"status\": \"implemented\",\n-      \"sourceBehavior\": \"LoginScreen observes Compose state from `viewModel.email` and `viewModel.password`, and it collects `eventFlow` in `LaunchedEffect` so text changes and failed-login snackbar events recompose immediately while the screen stays active.\",\n-      \"targetBehavior\": \"The HarmonyOS bootstrap route host preserves the same observable login-screen contract with `@State` fields for email, password, and error message. `renderLoginRoute` binds those values directly into `TextInput` components, clears stale errors when fields change, and re-renders immediately on invalid-login updates while keeping one-shot feedback through toast emission.\",\n-      \"verificationEvidence\": [\n-        \"Source review: D:/Kotlin2Cangjie/Foodike/app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/login/LoginScreen.kt reads `val email by viewModel.email`, `val password by viewModel.password`, and collects `eventFlow` inside `LaunchedEffect` to show snackbar feedback.\",\n-        \"Target review: entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj declares `@State` loginEmail, loginPassword, and loginErrorMessage, updates them from `renderLoginRoute`, and reuses them in `performLogin` and `clearLoginError`.\",\n-        \"Target review: entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/login/login_page.cj::renderLoginRoute binds the observed values into text inputs and the error banner so field edits and invalid-login state changes propagate immediately in the visible UI.\",\n-        \"Test verification: `C:/Users/Sieger/.cangjie-sdk/6.1/cangjie/build-tools/tools/bin/cjpm.exe test --target aarch64-linux-ohos` passed in `D:/workspace/Foodike/Foodike-Harmony/entry`, including `phase03_onboarding_login_profile_test.cj::Phase03OnboardingLoginProfileTest.loginStoreAcceptsOnlySourceCredentials`.\"\n-      ],\n-      \"parityLevel\": \"equivalent\",\n-      \"targetEndpoints\": [\n-        \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj::FoodikeBootstrap.loginEmail\",\n-        \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj::FoodikeBootstrap.loginPassword\",\n-        \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj::FoodikeBootstrap.loginErrorMessage\",\n-        \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj::FoodikeBootstrap.clearLoginError\",\n-        \"entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/login/login_page.cj::renderLoginRoute\"\n-      ],\n-      \"tests\": [\n-        \"entry/src/test/cangjie/phase03_onboarding_login_profile_test.cj::Phase03OnboardingLoginProfileTest.loginStoreAcceptsOnlySourceCredentials\"\n-      ],\n-      \"notes\": \"The target uses ArkUI `@State` in the route host instead of a separate ViewModel/SharedFlow pair, but it preserves the source-visible immediate field and error-state propagation.\"\n-    }\n-    }\n-  ]\n-}\n","additions":0,"deletions":154}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nD translation-inputs/agent-inputs/tmp-phase03-login-group-patch.json","time":{"start":1782387437306,"end":1782387437309}},"id":"prt_efe91eea4001ss96cAIu0FWt8J","sessionID":"ses_101725145ffej8BoFsdX6HrgJf","messageID":"msg_efe91ca20001gKZL4SY0gMl2Ix"}}
