     \"targetBehavior\": \"No HarmonyOS runtime-permission flow was added for the login route because this source login screen does not request permissions or call protected APIs.\",\n784:       \"verificationEvidence\": [\n785:         \"Source review: D:/Kotlin2Cangjie/Foodike/app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/login/LoginScreen.kt contains text fields, toasts, snackbar collection, and navController routing only.\",\n786:         \"Target review: entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/login/login_page.cj, login_store.cj, and app/bootstrap_page.cj contain no permission APIs or protected platform access.\"\n787:       ],\n788:       \"parityLevel\": \"not-applicable\",\n789:       \"targetEndpoints\": [],\n790:       \"tests\": [],\n791:       \"notes\": \"Static-analysis permission tagging for LoginScreen.kt was a false positive.\",\n792:       \"deferredReason\": \"\",\n793:       \"targetFallback\": \"\",\n794:       \"risk\": \"\",\n795:       \"futureCompletionPath\": \"\"\n796:     },\n797:     {\n798:       \"featureId\": \"app-src-main-java-com-example-foodike-presentation-login-2c65d08c3b-005-screen-lifecycle-entry-point-initializat\",\n799:       \"featureName\": \"Screen lifecycle, entry point initialization, resume/pause refresh, or teardown behavior.\",\n800:       \"sourcePath\": \"app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/login/LoginScreen.kt\",\n801:       \"importance\": \"critical\",\n802:       \"category\": \"kotlin-source\",\n803:       \"riskTags\": [\n804:         \"image_viewer\",\n805:         \"navigation_resource\",\n806:         \"notification_widget\",\n807:         \"permissions\",\n808:         \"screen_lifecycle\",\n809:         \"settings\",\n810:         \"state_model\"\n811:       ],\n812:       \"keyClasses\": [],\n813:       \"keyMethods\": [\n814:         \"LoginScreen\"\n815:       ],\n816:       \"androidIds\": [],\n817:       \"dependencies\": [],\n818:       \"featurePoint\": \"Screen lifecycle, entry point initialization, resume/pause refresh, or teardown behavior.\",\n819:       \"sourceEvidence\": \"path=app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/login/LoginScreen.kt; category=kotlin-source; importance=critical; keyMethods=LoginScreen; featurePoint=Screen lifecycle, entry point initialization, resume/pause refresh, or teardown behavior.\",\n820:       \"status\": \"implemented\",\n821:       \"plannedPhase\": \"phase-03-onboarding-login-profile\",\n822:       \"sourceBehavior\": \"LoginScreen performs screen-entry setup by creating scaffold state, wiring a `LaunchedEffect(key1 = true)` collector for one-shot UI events, and applying status/navigation bar colors while the login screen is active.\",\n823:       \"targetBehavior\": \"The HarmonyOS bootstrap route host performs login-screen entry setup by seeding dedicated login state fields, clearing stale error state as users edit, and centralizing login actions in the route host so the login page can be entered, dismissed, and revisited cleanly during onboarding/login/profile flow transitions. The target also preserves immediate one-shot user feedback on failed login through toast emission plus the visible inline error banner.\",\n824:       \"verificationEvidence\": [\n825:         \"Source review: D:/Kotlin2Cangjie/Foodike/app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/login/LoginScreen.kt initializes scaffold state, collects `eventFlow` in `LaunchedEffect`, and configures window colors from the active Activity context.\",\n826:         \"Target review: entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/app/bootstrap_page.cj::FoodikeBootstrap.buildLoginRoute, clearLoginError, and performLogin keep route-entry state and one-shot login feedback inside the route host used at runtime.\",\n827:         \"Target review: entry/src/main/cangjie/ohos_app_cangjie_entry/features/login/login_page.cj::buildLoginErrorBanner and renderLoginRoute preserve screen-local error presentation while bootstra